	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I found a solution to the connector problem.  I just sliced my 48 pin connectors down the middle splitting the two rows of pins in two.  It turns out that each side is just the right thickness to fit snugly between the expansion connector and its shell, so the two halves of the female socket don't have to be connected to ensure a good connection with the expansion bus.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
